        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         These issues are never going to be addressed as both of them are really non issues as they could lead to severe exploits.</P><P>Regarding your giving your friends weapon to your pet. You will notice the next time you initiate a trade with a Player controlled character or PC that the trade window always shows 8 slots for him and 8 slots for you.</P><P>When you intiate a trade with a Non-Player character or NPC the trade windows only has a single rows of 4 slots in which to place items you give to the NPC. </P><P>It is therefore extremely difficult to accidentally give stuff to an NPC unless you are a complete newbie (which you say you are). Nevertheless I am sure you will never make this mistake again.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
